description: JavaScript — avoid hot-path allocations (prefer caches) and keep cyclomatic complexity low
globs:
  - "**/*.js"
alwaysApply: false
---

# JS: hot paths & complexity

**Allocations (loops, ticks, handlers):** cache stable stuff at module/class scope; reuse pools/scratch, not new `[]`/`{}`/`.map`/`.filter`/`.slice` every call; indexed loops; less string churn. Skip for rare/init code.

**Complexity:** early returns / guards; small helpers; flatten nesting; tables/maps over long if-chains; less branching in hot paths.
